					"numinlets" : 1,
					"numoutlets" : 0,
					"patching_rect" : [ 40.0, 320.0, 860.0, 60.0 ],
					"text" : "Sit centered between the speakers at the stated span and distance — the cancellation is designed for that exact geometry and relaxes gracefully as you move. The cancelled path is ~12 dB quieter than bypass (the +12 dB filter-gain ceiling is repaid as static makeup attenuation) and 512 samples late (the filters' modeling delay), so loudness-match upstream before A/B judgments. Feed it binaural material (e.g. ambitap.binaural~ or ambitap.panbin~) for sources outside the speaker span; plain stereo simply widens."
				}

			}
, 			{
